---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Privacy Policy | Makor" description="How Makor collects, uses, and protects your personal information.">
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Makor</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: 17 July 2026</p>
  </section>

  <div class="legal">
    <p>This Privacy Policy explains how your personal information is collected, used, and protected when you use Makor (www.makor.co.za), a free Bible study website. Makor is operated by Luyanda Jafta, a private individual based in South Africa, who is the responsible party (data controller) for the purposes of this policy. You can reach us at any time at luyanda@fleetly.co.za.</p>

    <p>We keep this policy plain and honest, in the same spirit as the site itself. Please read it carefully, and contact us if anything is unclear.</p>

    <h2>Who this policy covers</h2>
    <p>This policy applies to everyone who visits Makor, whether or not you sign in. Makor is intended for a general audience. It is not directed at children, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 18 without the consent of a parent or guardian. If you believe a child has provided us information, contact us and we will remove it.</p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <h3>Account information</h3>
    <p>Signing in is optional. If you choose to sign in, we use Google Sign-In through our authentication provider, Supabase. When you sign in we receive from Google your name, your email address, and a Google account identifier. We never receive or store your Google password.</p>

    <h3>Your study progress</h3>
    <p>If you are signed in, we store the record of your learning so we can show you your growth: which studies you begin and complete, your quiz scores before and after each study, your selected answers, and the dates and times of those attempts. This information is linked to your account.</p>

    <h3>Technical information</h3>
    <p>Like most websites, our hosting and infrastructure providers automatically process limited technical data needed to deliver and secure the site, such as your device and browser type, general location inferred from your IP address, and standard server logs. Your browser also stores small amounts of data on your own device to keep you signed in and to remember interface preferences, such as whether you have minimized the header. We do not use advertising cookies or third-party tracking or analytics.</p>

    <h2>How we use your information</h2>
    <p>We use your information only to: provide the study service and let you sign in; save and display your progress and growth over time; keep the site secure and working correctly; and respond to you when you contact us. We do not sell your personal information, we do not share it for advertising, and we do not use it to build profiles for marketing.</p>

    <h2>Who processes your information for us</h2>
    <p>We rely on a small number of trusted service providers (operators, under POPIA) who process data on our behalf and under our instructions:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Google, for sign-in (authentication).</li>
      <li>Supabase, for authentication and for hosting the database that stores your account and progress.</li>
      <li>Cloudflare, for website hosting and content delivery.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>These providers may process and store information on servers located outside South Africa. Where that happens, we rely on their contractual and technical safeguards to protect your information to a standard comparable to South African law.</p>

    <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
    <p>We keep your account and progress information for as long as your account remains active, so that your growth record stays available to you. If you ask us to delete your account, we will delete your personal information within a reasonable period, except where we are required to retain limited records by law.</p>

    <h2>Your rights under POPIA</h2>
    <p>Under South Africa's Protection of Personal Information Act (POPIA) you have the right to: know what information we hold about you and to access it; ask us to correct or delete information that is inaccurate, irrelevant, or no longer needed; object to our processing in certain circumstances; and withdraw any consent you have given. To exercise any of these rights, email luyanda@fleetly.co.za and we will respond as soon as we reasonably can.</p>
    <p>If you are not satisfied with how we have handled your information, you may lodge a complaint with the Information Regulator of South Africa (https://inforegulator.org.za).</p>

    <h2>If you are in the European Union or United Kingdom</h2>
    <p>As a courtesy to visitors in the EU and UK, we note the following under the GDPR and UK GDPR. Our lawful bases for processing are your consent (for sign-in and storing your progress), our legitimate interest in operating and securing the site, and performance of the service you request. You have the rights of access, rectification, erasure, restriction, portability, and objection, and the right to withdraw consent at any time. You may also lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority. International transfers of your data are protected by the safeguards described above.</p>

    <h2>Security</h2>
    <p>We take reasonable and appropriate measures to protect your information, and we rely on providers who do the same. No method of transmission or storage is completely secure, however, so we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy from time to time. When we do, we will change the date at the top of this page, and significant changes will be reflected here. Your continued use of Makor after an update means you accept the revised policy.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>For any question about this policy or your personal information, contact Luyanda Jafta at luyanda@fleetly.co.za.</p>

    <p class="backlink"><a href="/">Back to Makor</a></p>
  </div>
</Base>
